This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces a novel training principle for probabilistic models that is an alternative to maximum likelihood. The paper also discusses the use of backpropagation for training the proposed Generative Stochastic Networks (GSN) framework. Additionally, the paper includes experiments on image datasets, which are commonly used in the field of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of Markov chains, which are commonly used in the field of natural language processing (cs.NE) and statistical learning (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses the use of dependency networks and generalized pseudolikelihood, which are commonly used in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
